208 bool Document::undo(int id)
209 {
210  if (d->iUndoMode) {
211  if (id) {
212  auto it = mUndoMap.find(id);
213  if (it == mUndoMap.end()) {
214  return false;
215  }
216  if (it->second != d->activeUndoTransaction) {
217  while (!mUndoTransactions.empty() && mUndoTransactions.back() != it->second) {
218  undo(0);
219  }
220  }
221  }
222 
223  if (d->activeUndoTransaction) {
224  _commitTransaction(true);
225  }
226  if (mUndoTransactions.empty()) {
227  return false;
228  }
229  // redo
230  d->activeUndoTransaction = new Transaction(mUndoTransactions.back()->getID());
231  d->activeUndoTransaction->Name = mUndoTransactions.back()->Name;
232 
233  {
234  Base::FlagToggler<bool> flag(d->undoing);
235  // applying the undo
236  mUndoTransactions.back()->apply(*this, false);
237 
238  // save the redo
239  mRedoMap[d->activeUndoTransaction->getID()] = d->activeUndoTransaction;
240  mRedoTransactions.push_back(d->activeUndoTransaction);
241  d->activeUndoTransaction = nullptr;
242 
243  mUndoMap.erase(mUndoTransactions.back()->getID());
244  delete mUndoTransactions.back();
245  mUndoTransactions.pop_back();
246  }
247 
248  for (auto& obj : d->objectArray) {
249  if (obj->testStatus(ObjectStatus::PendingTransactionUpdate)) {
250  obj->onUndoRedoFinished();
251  obj->setStatus(ObjectStatus::PendingTransactionUpdate, false);
252  }
253  }
254 
255  signalUndo(*this); // now signal the undo
256 
257  return true;
258  }
259 
260  return false;
261 }
262 
263 bool Document::redo(int id)
264 {
265  if (d->iUndoMode) {
266  if (id) {
267  auto it = mRedoMap.find(id);
268  if (it == mRedoMap.end()) {
269  return false;
270  }
271  while (!mRedoTransactions.empty() && mRedoTransactions.back() != it->second) {
272  redo(0);
273  }
274  }
275 
276  if (d->activeUndoTransaction) {
277  _commitTransaction(true);
278  }
279 
280  assert(mRedoTransactions.size() != 0);
281 
282  // undo
283  d->activeUndoTransaction = new Transaction(mRedoTransactions.back()->getID());
284  d->activeUndoTransaction->Name = mRedoTransactions.back()->Name;
285 
286  // do the redo
287  {
288  Base::FlagToggler<bool> flag(d->undoing);
289  mRedoTransactions.back()->apply(*this, true);
290 
291  mUndoMap[d->activeUndoTransaction->getID()] = d->activeUndoTransaction;
292  mUndoTransactions.push_back(d->activeUndoTransaction);
293  d->activeUndoTransaction = nullptr;
294 
295  mRedoMap.erase(mRedoTransactions.back()->getID());
296  delete mRedoTransactions.back();
297  mRedoTransactions.pop_back();
298  }
299 
300  for (auto& obj : d->objectArray) {
301  if (obj->testStatus(ObjectStatus::PendingTransactionUpdate)) {
302  obj->onUndoRedoFinished();
303  obj->setStatus(ObjectStatus::PendingTransactionUpdate, false);
304  }
305  }
306 
307  signalRedo(*this);
308  return true;
309  }
310 
311  return false;
312 }

314 void Document::addOrRemovePropertyOfObject(TransactionalObject* obj, Property* prop, bool add)
315 {
316  if (!prop || !obj || !obj->isAttachedToDocument()) {
317  return;
318  }
319  if (d->iUndoMode && !isPerformingTransaction() && !d->activeUndoTransaction) {
320  if (!testStatus(Restoring) || testStatus(Importing)) {
321  int tid = 0;
322  const char* name = GetApplication().getActiveTransaction(&tid);
323  if (name && tid > 0) {
324  _openTransaction(name, tid);
325  }
326  }
327  }
328  if (d->activeUndoTransaction && !d->rollback) {
329  d->activeUndoTransaction->addOrRemoveProperty(obj, prop, add);
330  }
331 }

364 {

366  if (FC_LOG_INSTANCE.isEnabled(FC_LOGLEVEL_LOG)) {
367  FC_WARN("Cannot open transaction while transacting");

375 int Document::_openTransaction(const char* name, int id)
376 {
377  if (isPerformingTransaction() || d->committing) {
378  if (FC_LOG_INSTANCE.isEnabled(FC_LOGLEVEL_LOG)) {
379  FC_WARN("Cannot open transaction while transacting");
380  }
381  return 0;
382  }
383 
384  if (d->iUndoMode) {
385  // Avoid recursive calls that is possible while
386  // clearing the redo transactions and will cause
387  // a double deletion of some transaction and thus
388  // a segmentation fault
389  if (d->opentransaction) {
390  return 0;
391  }
392  Base::FlagToggler<> flag(d->opentransaction);
393 
394  if (id && mUndoMap.find(id) != mUndoMap.end()) {
395  throw Base::RuntimeError("invalid transaction id");
396  }
397  if (d->activeUndoTransaction) {
398  _commitTransaction(true);
399  }
400  _clearRedos();
401 
402  d->activeUndoTransaction = new Transaction(id);
403  if (!name) {
404  name = "<empty>";
405  }
406  d->activeUndoTransaction->Name = name;
407  mUndoMap[d->activeUndoTransaction->getID()] = d->activeUndoTransaction;
408  id = d->activeUndoTransaction->getID();
409 
410  signalOpenTransaction(*this, name);
411 
412  auto& app = GetApplication();
413  auto activeDoc = app.getActiveDocument();
414  if (activeDoc && activeDoc != this && !activeDoc->hasPendingTransaction()) {
415  std::string aname("-> ");
416  aname += d->activeUndoTransaction->Name;
417  FC_LOG("auto transaction " << getName() << " -> " << activeDoc->getName());
418  activeDoc->_openTransaction(aname.c_str(), id);
419  }
420  return id;
421  }
422  return 0;
423 }

430  }
431  else {

438 void Document::_checkTransaction(DocumentObject* pcDelObj, const Property* What, int line)
439 {
440  // if the undo is active but no transaction open, open one!
441  if (d->iUndoMode && !isPerformingTransaction()) {
442  if (!d->activeUndoTransaction) {
443  if (!testStatus(Restoring) || testStatus(Importing)) {
444  int tid = 0;
445  const char* name = GetApplication().getActiveTransaction(&tid);
446  if (name && tid > 0) {
447  bool ignore = false;
448  if (What && What->testStatus(Property::NoModify)) {
449  ignore = true;
450  }
451  if (FC_LOG_INSTANCE.isEnabled(FC_LOGLEVEL_LOG)) {
452  if (What) {
453  FC_LOG((ignore ? "ignore" : "auto")
454  << " transaction (" << line << ") '" << What->getFullName());
455  }
456  else {
457  FC_LOG((ignore ? "ignore" : "auto") << " transaction (" << line << ") '"
458  << name << "' in " << getName());
459  }
460  }
461  if (!ignore) {
462  _openTransaction(name, tid);
463  }
464  return;
465  }
466  }
467  if (!pcDelObj) {
468  return;
469  }
470  // When the object is going to be deleted we have to check if it has already been added
471  // to the undo transactions
472  std::list<Transaction*>::iterator it;
473  for (it = mUndoTransactions.begin(); it != mUndoTransactions.end(); ++it) {
474  if ((*it)->hasObject(pcDelObj)) {
475  _openTransaction("Delete");
476  break;
477  }
478  }
479  }
480  }
481 }

497 void Document::commitTransaction()
498 {
499  if (isPerformingTransaction() || d->committing) {
500  if (FC_LOG_INSTANCE.isEnabled(FC_LOGLEVEL_LOG)) {
501  FC_WARN("Cannot commit transaction while transacting");
502  }
503  return;
504  }
505 
506  if (d->activeUndoTransaction) {
507  GetApplication().closeActiveTransaction(false, d->activeUndoTransaction->getID());
508  }

510 
511 void Document::_commitTransaction(bool notify)
512 {
513  if (isPerformingTransaction()) {
514  if (FC_LOG_INSTANCE.isEnabled(FC_LOGLEVEL_LOG)) {
515  FC_WARN("Cannot commit transaction while transacting");
516  }
517  return;
518  }
519  else if (d->committing) {
520  // for a recursive call return without printing a warning
521  return;
522  }
523 
524  if (d->activeUndoTransaction) {
525  Base::FlagToggler<> flag(d->committing);
526  Application::TransactionSignaller signaller(false, true);
527  int id = d->activeUndoTransaction->getID();
528  mUndoTransactions.push_back(d->activeUndoTransaction);
529  d->activeUndoTransaction = nullptr;
530  // check the stack for the limits
531  if (mUndoTransactions.size() > d->UndoMaxStackSize) {
532  mUndoMap.erase(mUndoTransactions.front()->getID());
533  delete mUndoTransactions.front();
534  mUndoTransactions.pop_front();
535  }
536  signalCommitTransaction(*this);
537 
538  // closeActiveTransaction() may call again _commitTransaction()
539  if (notify) {
540  GetApplication().closeActiveTransaction(false, id);
541  }
542  }
543 }

558 void Document::_abortTransaction()
559 {
560  if (isPerformingTransaction() || d->committing) {
561  if (FC_LOG_INSTANCE.isEnabled(FC_LOGLEVEL_LOG)) {
562  FC_WARN("Cannot abort transaction while transacting");
563  }
564  }
565 
566  if (d->activeUndoTransaction) {
567  Base::FlagToggler<bool> flag(d->rollback);
568  Application::TransactionSignaller signaller(true, true);
569 
570  // applying the so far made changes
571  d->activeUndoTransaction->apply(*this, false);
572 
573  // destroy the undo
574  mUndoMap.erase(d->activeUndoTransaction->getID());
575  delete d->activeUndoTransaction;
576  d->activeUndoTransaction = nullptr;
577  signalAbortTransaction(*this);
578  }
579 }

591 int Document::getTransactionID(bool undo, unsigned pos) const
592 {
593  if (undo) {
594  if (d->activeUndoTransaction) {
595  if (pos == 0) {
596  return d->activeUndoTransaction->getID();
597  }
598  --pos;
599  }
600  if (pos >= mUndoTransactions.size()) {
601  return 0;
602  }
603  auto rit = mUndoTransactions.rbegin();
604  for (; pos; ++rit, --pos) {
605  continue;
606  }
607  return (*rit)->getID();
608  }
609  if (pos >= mRedoTransactions.size()) {
610  return 0;
611  }
612  auto rit = mRedoTransactions.rbegin();
613  for (; pos; ++rit, --pos) {}
614  return (*rit)->getID();
615 }

655 void Document::clearUndos()
656 {
657  if (isPerformingTransaction() || d->committing) {
658  FC_ERR("Cannot clear undos while transacting");
659  return;
660  }
661 
662  if (d->activeUndoTransaction) {
663  _commitTransaction(true);
664  }
665 
666  mUndoMap.clear();
667 
668  // When cleaning up the undo stack we must delete the transactions from front
669  // to back because a document object can appear in several transactions but
670  // once removed from the document the object can never ever appear in any later
671  // transaction. Since the document object may be also deleted when the transaction
672  // is deleted we must make sure not access an object once it's destroyed. Thus, we
673  // go from front to back and not the other way round.
674  while (!mUndoTransactions.empty()) {
675  delete mUndoTransactions.front();
676  mUndoTransactions.pop_front();
677  }
678  // while (!mUndoTransactions.empty()) {
679  // delete mUndoTransactions.back();
680  // mUndoTransactions.pop_back();
681  // }
682 
683  _clearRedos();
684 }

686 int Document::getAvailableUndos(int id) const
687 {
688  if (id) {
689  auto it = mUndoMap.find(id);
690  if (it == mUndoMap.end()) {
691  return 0;
692  }
693  int i = 0;
694  if (d->activeUndoTransaction) {
695  ++i;
696  if (d->activeUndoTransaction->getID() == id) {
697  return i;
698  }
699  }
700  auto rit = mUndoTransactions.rbegin();
701  for (; rit != mUndoTransactions.rend() && *rit != it->second; ++rit) {
702  ++i;
703  }
704  assert(rit != mUndoTransactions.rend());
705  return i + 1;
706  }
707  if (d->activeUndoTransaction) {
708  return static_cast<int>(mUndoTransactions.size() + 1);
709  }
710  else {
711  return static_cast<int>(mUndoTransactions.size());
712  }
713 }

715 int Document::getAvailableRedos(int id) const
716 {
717  if (id) {
718  auto it = mRedoMap.find(id);
719  if (it == mRedoMap.end()) {
720  return 0;
721  }
722  int i = 0;
723  for (auto rit = mRedoTransactions.rbegin(); *rit != it->second; ++rit) {
724  ++i;
725  }
726  assert(i < (int)mRedoTransactions.size());
727  return i + 1;
728  }
729  return static_cast<int>(mRedoTransactions.size());
730 }

781  App::GetApplication().signalRelabelDocument(*this);

783  else if (prop == &ShowHidden) {
784  App::GetApplication().signalShowHidden(*this);
785  }
786  else if (prop == &Uid) {
787  std::string new_dir =
788  getTransientDirectoryName(this->Uid.getValueStr(), this->FileName.getStrValue());
789  std::string old_dir = this->TransientDir.getStrValue();
790  Base::FileInfo TransDirNew(new_dir);
791  Base::FileInfo TransDirOld(old_dir);
792  // this directory should not exist
793  if (!TransDirNew.exists()) {
794  if (TransDirOld.exists()) {
795  if (!TransDirOld.renameFile(new_dir.c_str())) {
796  Base::Console().Warning("Failed to rename '%s' to '%s'\n",
797  old_dir.c_str(),
798  new_dir.c_str());
799  }
800  else {
801  this->TransientDir.setValue(new_dir);
802  }
803  }
804  else {
805  if (!TransDirNew.createDirectories()) {
806  Base::Console().Warning("Failed to create '%s'\n", new_dir.c_str());
807  }
808  else {
809  this->TransientDir.setValue(new_dir);
810  }
811  }
812  }
813  // when reloading an existing document the transient directory doesn't change
814  // so we must avoid to generate a new uuid
815  else if (TransDirNew.filePath() != TransDirOld.filePath()) {
816  // make sure that the uuid is unique
817  std::string uuid = this->Uid.getValueStr();
818  Base::Uuid id;
819  Base::Console().Warning("Document with the UUID '%s' already exists, change to '%s'\n",
820  uuid.c_str(),
821  id.getValue().c_str());
822  // recursive call of onChanged()
823  this->Uid.setValue(id);
824  }
825  }
826  else if (prop == &UseHasher) {
827  for (auto obj : d->objectArray) {
828  auto geofeature = dynamic_cast<GeoFeature*>(obj);
829  if (geofeature && geofeature->getPropertyOfGeometry()) {
830  geofeature->enforceRecompute();
831  }
832  }
833  }
834 }

974 Document::~Document()
975 {
976 #ifdef FC_LOGUPDATECHAIN
977  Console().Log("-App::Document: %s %p\n", getName(), this);
978 #endif
979 
980  try {
981  clearUndos();
982  }
983  catch (const boost::exception&) {
984  }
985 
986 #ifdef FC_LOGUPDATECHAIN
987  Console().Log("-Delete Features of %s \n", getName());
988 #endif
989 
990  d->clearDocument();
991 
992  // Remark: The API of Py::Object has been changed to set whether the wrapper owns the passed
993  // Python object or not. In the constructor we forced the wrapper to own the object so we need
994  // not to dec'ref the Python object any more.
995  // But we must still invalidate the Python object because it doesn't need to be
996  // destructed right now because the interpreter can own several references to it.
997  Base::PyGILStateLocker lock;
998  Base::PyObjectBase* doc = static_cast<Base::PyObjectBase*>(d->DocumentPythonObject.ptr());
999  // Call before decrementing the reference counter, otherwise a heap error can occur
1000  doc->setInvalid();
1001 
1002  // remove Transient directory
1003  try {
1004  Base::FileInfo TransDir(TransientDir.getValue());
1005  TransDir.deleteDirectoryRecursive();
1006  }
1007  catch (const Base::Exception& e) {
1008  std::cerr << "Removing transient directory failed: " << e.what() << std::endl;
1009  }
1010  delete d;
1011 }

1013 std::string Document::getTransientDirectoryName(const std::string& uuid,
1014  const std::string& filename) const
1015 {
1016  // Create a directory name of the form: {ExeName}_Doc_{UUID}_{HASH}_{PID}
1017  std::stringstream out;
1018  QCryptographicHash hash(QCryptographicHash::Sha1);
1019 #if QT_VERSION < QT_VERSION_CHECK(6, 3, 0)
1020  hash.addData(filename.c_str(), filename.size());
1021 #else
1022  hash.addData(QByteArrayView(filename.c_str(), filename.size()));
1023 #endif
1024  out << App::Application::getUserCachePath() << App::Application::getExecutableName() << "_Doc_"
1025  << uuid << "_" << hash.result().toHex().left(6).constData() << "_"
1026  << App::Application::applicationPid();
1027  return out.str();
1028 }

1064 void Document::Restore(Base::XMLReader& reader)
1065 {
1066  int i, Cnt;
1067  d->hashers.clear();
1068  d->touchedObjs.clear();
1069  addStringHasher(d->Hasher);
1070  setStatus(Document::PartialDoc, false);
1071 
1072  reader.readElement("Document");
1073  long scheme = reader.getAttributeAsInteger("SchemaVersion");
1074  reader.DocumentSchema = scheme;
1075  if (reader.hasAttribute("ProgramVersion")) {
1076  reader.ProgramVersion = reader.getAttribute("ProgramVersion");
1077  }
1078  else {
1079  reader.ProgramVersion = "pre-0.14";
1080  }
1081  if (reader.hasAttribute("FileVersion")) {
1082  reader.FileVersion = reader.getAttributeAsUnsigned("FileVersion");
1083  }
1084  else {
1085  reader.FileVersion = 0;
1086  }
1087 
1088  if (reader.hasAttribute("StringHasher")) {
1089  d->Hasher->Restore(reader);
1090  }
1091  else {
1092  d->Hasher->clear();
1093  }
1094 
1095  // When this document was created the FileName and Label properties
1096  // were set to the absolute path or file name, respectively. To save
1097  // the document to the file it was loaded from or to show the file name
1098  // in the tree view we must restore them after loading the file because
1099  // they will be overridden.
1100  // Note: This does not affect the internal name of the document in any way
1101  // that is kept in Application.
1102  std::string FilePath = FileName.getValue();
1103  std::string DocLabel = Label.getValue();
1104 
1105  // read the Document Properties, when reading in Uid the transient directory gets renamed
1106  // automatically
1107  PropertyContainer::Restore(reader);
1108 
1109  // We must restore the correct 'FileName' property again because the stored
1110  // value could be invalid.
1111  FileName.setValue(FilePath.c_str());
1112  Label.setValue(DocLabel.c_str());
1113 
1114  // SchemeVersion "2"
1115  if (scheme == 2) {
1116  // read the feature types
1117  reader.readElement("Features");
1118  Cnt = reader.getAttributeAsInteger("Count");
1119  for (i = 0; i < Cnt; i++) {
1120  reader.readElement("Feature");
1121  string type = reader.getAttribute("type");
1122  string name = reader.getAttribute("name");
1123  try {
1124  addObject(type.c_str(), name.c_str(), /*isNew=*/false);
1125  }
1126  catch (Base::Exception&) {
1127  Base::Console().Message("Cannot create object '%s'\n", name.c_str());
1128  }
1129  }
1130  reader.readEndElement("Features");
1131 
1132  // read the features itself
1133  reader.readElement("FeatureData");
1134  Cnt = reader.getAttributeAsInteger("Count");
1135  for (i = 0; i < Cnt; i++) {
1136  reader.readElement("Feature");
1137  string name = reader.getAttribute("name");
1138  DocumentObject* pObj = getObject(name.c_str());
1139  if (pObj) { // check if this feature has been registered
1140  pObj->setStatus(ObjectStatus::Restore, true);
1141  pObj->Restore(reader);
1142  pObj->setStatus(ObjectStatus::Restore, false);
1143  }
1144  reader.readEndElement("Feature");
1145  }
1146  reader.readEndElement("FeatureData");
1147  } // SchemeVersion "3" or higher
1148  else if (scheme >= 3) {
1149  // read the feature types
1150  readObjects(reader);
1151 
1152  // tip object handling. First the whole document has to be read, then we
1153  // can restore the Tip link out of the TipName Property:
1154  Tip.setValue(getObject(TipName.getValue()));
1155  }
1156 
1157  reader.readEndElement("Document");
1158 }

1171 std::pair<bool, int> Document::addStringHasher(const StringHasherRef& hasher) const
1172 {
1173  if (!hasher) {
1174  return std::make_pair(false, 0);
1175  }
1176  auto ret =
1177  d->hashers.left.insert(HasherMap::left_map::value_type(hasher, (int)d->hashers.size()));
1178  if (ret.second) {
1179  hasher->clearMarks();
1180  }
1181  return std::make_pair(ret.second, ret.first->second);
1182 }

1184 StringHasherRef Document::getStringHasher(int idx) const
1185 {
1186  StringHasherRef hasher;
1187  if (idx < 0) {
1188  if (UseHasher.getValue()) {
1189  return d->Hasher;
1190  }
1191  return hasher;
1192  }
1193  auto it = d->hashers.right.find(idx);
1194  if (it == d->hashers.right.end()) {
1195  hasher = new StringHasher;
1196  d->hashers.right.insert(HasherMap::right_map::value_type(idx, hasher));
1197  }
1198  else {
1199  hasher = it->second;
1200  }
1201  return hasher;
1202 }

1229 // The current implementation choose to use a static variable for exporting
1230 // status because we can be exporting multiple objects from multiple documents
1231 // at the same time. I see no benefits in distinguish which documents are
1232 // exporting, so just use a static variable for global status. But the
1233 // implementation can easily be changed here if necessary.
1234 Document::ExportStatus Document::isExporting(const App::DocumentObject* obj) const
1235 {
1236  if (_ExportStatus.status != Document::NotExporting
1237  && (!obj || _ExportStatus.objs.find(obj) != _ExportStatus.objs.end())) {
1238  return _ExportStatus.status;

1279  writeObjects(obj, writer);

1297 void Document::writeObjects(const std::vector<App::DocumentObject*>& obj,
1298  Base::Writer& writer) const
1299 {
1300  // writing the features types
1301  writer.incInd(); // indentation for 'Objects count'
1302  writer.Stream() << writer.ind() << "<Objects Count=\"" << obj.size();
1303  if (!isExporting(nullptr)) {
1304  writer.Stream() << "\" " FC_ATTR_DEPENDENCIES "=\"1";
1305  }
1306  writer.Stream() << "\">" << endl;
1307 
1308  writer.incInd(); // indentation for 'Object type'
1309 
1310  if (!isExporting(nullptr)) {
1311  for (auto o : obj) {
1312  const auto& outList =
1313  o->getOutList(DocumentObject::OutListNoHidden | DocumentObject::OutListNoXLinked);
1314  writer.Stream() << writer.ind()
1315  << "<" FC_ELEMENT_OBJECT_DEPS " " FC_ATTR_DEP_OBJ_NAME "=\""
1316  << o->getNameInDocument() << "\" " FC_ATTR_DEP_COUNT "=\""
1317  << outList.size();
1318  if (outList.empty()) {
1319  writer.Stream() << "\"/>" << endl;
1320  continue;
1321  }
1322  int partial = o->canLoadPartial();
1323  if (partial > 0) {
1324  writer.Stream() << "\" " FC_ATTR_DEP_ALLOW_PARTIAL << "=\"" << partial;
1325  }
1326  writer.Stream() << "\">" << endl;
1327  writer.incInd();
1328  for (auto dep : outList) {
1329  auto name = dep ? dep->getNameInDocument() : "";
1330  writer.Stream() << writer.ind()
1331  << "<" FC_ELEMENT_OBJECT_DEP " " FC_ATTR_DEP_OBJ_NAME "=\""
1332  << (name ? name : "") << "\"/>" << endl;
1333  }
1334  writer.decInd();
1335  writer.Stream() << writer.ind() << "</" FC_ELEMENT_OBJECT_DEPS ">" << endl;
1336  }
1337  }
1338 
1339  std::vector<DocumentObject*>::const_iterator it;
1340  for (it = obj.begin(); it != obj.end(); ++it) {
1341  writer.Stream() << writer.ind() << "<Object "
1342  << "type=\"" << (*it)->getTypeId().getName() << "\" "
1343  << "name=\"" << (*it)->getExportName() << "\" "
1344  << "id=\"" << (*it)->getID() << "\" ";
1345 
1346  // Only write out custom view provider types
1347  std::string viewType = (*it)->getViewProviderNameStored();
1348  if (viewType != (*it)->getViewProviderName()) {
1349  writer.Stream() << "ViewType=\"" << viewType << "\" ";
1350  }
1351 
1352  // See DocumentObjectPy::getState
1353  if ((*it)->testStatus(ObjectStatus::Touch)) {
1354  writer.Stream() << "Touched=\"1\" ";
1355  }
1356  if ((*it)->testStatus(ObjectStatus::Error)) {
1357  writer.Stream() << "Invalid=\"1\" ";
1358  auto desc = getErrorDescription(*it);
1359  if (desc) {
1360  writer.Stream() << "Error=\"" << Property::encodeAttribute(desc) << "\" ";
1361  }
1362  }
1363  writer.Stream() << "/>" << endl;
1364  }
1365 
1366  writer.decInd(); // indentation for 'Object type'
1367  writer.Stream() << writer.ind() << "</Objects>" << endl;
1368 
1369  // writing the features itself
1370  writer.Stream() << writer.ind() << "<ObjectData Count=\"" << obj.size() << "\">" << endl;
1371 
1372  writer.incInd(); // indentation for 'Object name'
1373  for (it = obj.begin(); it != obj.end(); ++it) {
1374  writer.Stream() << writer.ind() << "<Object name=\"" << (*it)->getExportName() << "\"";
1375  if ((*it)->hasExtensions()) {
1376  writer.Stream() << " Extensions=\"True\"";
1377  }
1378 
1379  writer.Stream() << ">" << endl;
1380  (*it)->Save(writer);
1381  writer.Stream() << writer.ind() << "</Object>" << endl;
1382  }
1383 
1384  writer.decInd(); // indentation for 'Object name'
1385  writer.Stream() << writer.ind() << "</ObjectData>" << endl;
1386  writer.decInd(); // indentation for 'Objects count'
1387 }

1395 static void _loadDeps(const std::string& name,
1396  std::unordered_map<std::string, bool>& objs,
1397  const std::unordered_map<std::string, DepInfo>& deps)
1398 {
1399  auto it = deps.find(name);
1400  if (it == deps.end()) {
1401  objs.emplace(name, true);
1402  return;
1403  }
1404  if (it->second.canLoadPartial) {
1405  if (it->second.canLoadPartial == 1) {
1406  // canLoadPartial==1 means all its children will be created but not
1407  // restored, i.e. exists as if newly created object, and therefore no
1408  // need to load dependency of the children
1409  for (auto& dep : it->second.deps) {
1410  objs.emplace(dep, false);
1411  }
1412  objs.emplace(name, true);
1413  }
1414  else {
1415  objs.emplace(name, false);
1416  }
1417  return;
1418  }
1419  objs[name] = true;
1420  // If cannot load partial, then recurse to load all children dependency
1421  for (auto& dep : it->second.deps) {
1422  auto it = objs.find(dep);
1423  if (it != objs.end() && it->second) {
1424  continue;
1425  }
1426  _loadDeps(dep, objs, deps);
1427  }
1428 }

1430 std::vector<App::DocumentObject*> Document::readObjects(Base::XMLReader& reader)
1431 {
1432  d->touchedObjs.clear();
1433  bool keepDigits = testStatus(Document::KeepTrailingDigits);
1434  setStatus(Document::KeepTrailingDigits, !reader.doNameMapping());
1435  std::vector<App::DocumentObject*> objs;
1436 
1437 
1438  // read the object types
1439  reader.readElement("Objects");
1440  int Cnt = reader.getAttributeAsInteger("Count");
1441 
1442  if (!reader.hasAttribute(FC_ATTR_DEPENDENCIES)) {
1443  d->partialLoadObjects.clear();
1444  }
1445  else if (!d->partialLoadObjects.empty()) {
1446  std::unordered_map<std::string, DepInfo> deps;
1447  for (int i = 0; i < Cnt; i++) {
1448  reader.readElement(FC_ELEMENT_OBJECT_DEPS);
1449  int dcount = reader.getAttributeAsInteger(FC_ATTR_DEP_COUNT);
1450  if (!dcount) {
1451  continue;
1452  }
1453  auto& info = deps[reader.getAttribute(FC_ATTR_DEP_OBJ_NAME)];
1454  if (reader.hasAttribute(FC_ATTR_DEP_ALLOW_PARTIAL)) {
1455  info.canLoadPartial = reader.getAttributeAsInteger(FC_ATTR_DEP_ALLOW_PARTIAL);
1456  }
1457  for (int j = 0; j < dcount; ++j) {
1458  reader.readElement(FC_ELEMENT_OBJECT_DEP);
1459  const char* name = reader.getAttribute(FC_ATTR_DEP_OBJ_NAME);
1460  if (name && name[0]) {
1461  info.deps.insert(name);
1462  }
1463  }
1464  reader.readEndElement(FC_ELEMENT_OBJECT_DEPS);
1465  }
1466  std::vector<std::string> objs;
1467  objs.reserve(d->partialLoadObjects.size());
1468  for (auto& v : d->partialLoadObjects) {
1469  objs.emplace_back(v.first.c_str());
1470  }
1471  for (auto& name : objs) {
1472  _loadDeps(name, d->partialLoadObjects, deps);
1473  }
1474  if (Cnt > (int)d->partialLoadObjects.size()) {
1475  setStatus(Document::PartialDoc, true);
1476  }
1477  else {
1478  for (auto& v : d->partialLoadObjects) {
1479  if (!v.second) {
1480  setStatus(Document::PartialDoc, true);
1481  break;
1482  }
1483  }
1484  if (!testStatus(Document::PartialDoc)) {
1485  d->partialLoadObjects.clear();
1486  }
1487  }
1488  }
1489 
1490  long lastId = 0;
1491  for (int i = 0; i < Cnt; i++) {
1492  reader.readElement("Object");
1493  std::string type = reader.getAttribute("type");
1494  std::string name = reader.getAttribute("name");
1495  std::string viewType =
1496  reader.hasAttribute("ViewType") ? reader.getAttribute("ViewType") : "";
1497 
1498  bool partial = false;
1499  if (!d->partialLoadObjects.empty()) {
1500  auto it = d->partialLoadObjects.find(name);
1501  if (it == d->partialLoadObjects.end()) {
1502  continue;
1503  }
1504  partial = !it->second;
1505  }
1506 
1507  if (!testStatus(Status::Importing) && reader.hasAttribute("id")) {
1508  // if not importing, then temporary reset lastObjectId and make the
1509  // following addObject() generate the correct id for this object.
1510  d->lastObjectId = reader.getAttributeAsInteger("id") - 1;
1511  }
1512 
1513  // To prevent duplicate name when export/import of objects from
1514  // external documents, we append those external object name with
1515  // @<document name>. Before importing (here means we are called by
1516  // importObjects), we shall strip the postfix. What the caller
1517  // (MergeDocument) sees is still the unstripped name mapped to a new
1518  // internal name, and the rest of the link properties will be able to
1519  // correctly unmap the names.
1520  auto pos = name.find('@');
1521  std::string _obj_name;
1522  const char* obj_name;
1523  if (pos != std::string::npos) {
1524  _obj_name = name.substr(0, pos);
1525  obj_name = _obj_name.c_str();
1526  }
1527  else {
1528  obj_name = name.c_str();
1529  }
1530 
1531  try {
1532  // Use name from XML as is and do NOT remove trailing digits because
1533  // otherwise we may cause a dependency to itself
1534  // Example: Object 'Cut001' references object 'Cut' and removing the
1535  // digits we make an object 'Cut' referencing itself.
1536  App::DocumentObject* obj =
1537  addObject(type.c_str(), obj_name, /*isNew=*/false, viewType.c_str(), partial);
1538  if (obj) {
1539  if (lastId < obj->_Id) {
1540  lastId = obj->_Id;
1541  }
1542  objs.push_back(obj);
1543  // use this name for the later access because an object with
1544  // the given name may already exist
1545  reader.addName(name.c_str(), obj->getNameInDocument());
1546 
1547  // restore touch/error status flags
1548  if (reader.hasAttribute("Touched")) {
1549  if (reader.getAttributeAsInteger("Touched") != 0) {
1550  d->touchedObjs.insert(obj);
1551  }
1552  }
1553  if (reader.hasAttribute("Invalid")) {
1554  obj->setStatus(ObjectStatus::Error,
1555  reader.getAttributeAsInteger("Invalid") != 0);
1556  if (obj->isError() && reader.hasAttribute("Error")) {
1557  d->addRecomputeLog(reader.getAttribute("Error"), obj);
1558  }
1559  }
1560  }
1561  }
1562  catch (const Base::Exception& e) {
1563  Base::Console().Error("Cannot create object '%s': (%s)\n", name.c_str(), e.what());
1564  }
1565  }
1566  if (!testStatus(Status::Importing)) {
1567  d->lastObjectId = lastId;
1568  }
1569 
1570  reader.readEndElement("Objects");
1571  setStatus(Document::KeepTrailingDigits, keepDigits);
1572 
1573  // read the features itself
1574  reader.clearPartialRestoreDocumentObject();
1575  reader.readElement("ObjectData");
1576  Cnt = reader.getAttributeAsInteger("Count");
1577  for (int i = 0; i < Cnt; i++) {
1578  reader.readElement("Object");
1579  std::string name = reader.getName(reader.getAttribute("name"));
1580  DocumentObject* pObj = getObject(name.c_str());
1581  if (pObj
1582  && !pObj->testStatus(
1583  App::PartialObject)) { // check if this feature has been registered
1584  pObj->setStatus(ObjectStatus::Restore, true);
1585  try {
1586  FC_TRACE("restoring " << pObj->getFullName());
1587  pObj->Restore(reader);
1588  }
1589  // Try to continue only for certain exception types if not handled
1590  // by the feature type. For all other exception types abort the process.
1591  catch (const Base::UnicodeError& e) {
1592  e.ReportException();
1593  }
1594  catch (const Base::ValueError& e) {
1595  e.ReportException();
1596  }
1597  catch (const Base::IndexError& e) {
1598  e.ReportException();
1599  }
1600  catch (const Base::RuntimeError& e) {
1601  e.ReportException();
1602  }
1603  catch (const Base::XMLAttributeError& e) {
1604  e.ReportException();
1605  }
1606 
1607  pObj->setStatus(ObjectStatus::Restore, false);
1608 
1609  if (reader.testStatus(Base::XMLReader::ReaderStatus::PartialRestoreInDocumentObject)) {
1610  Base::Console().Error("Object \"%s\" was subject to a partial restore. As a result "
1611  "geometry may have changed or be incomplete.\n",
1612  name.c_str());
1613  reader.clearPartialRestoreDocumentObject();
1614  }
1615  }
1616  reader.readEndElement("Object");
1617  }
1618  reader.readEndElement("ObjectData");
1619 
1620  return objs;
1621 }

1626  setStatus(Status::RecomputeOnRestore, true);
1627  d->touchedObjs.insert(obj);
1628  obj->touch();

1684

1689  o->setStatus(App::ObjImporting, false);
1690  }
1691  }
1692 
1693  d->hashers.clear();
1694  return objs;
1695 }

1801 namespace App
1802 {
1803 // Helper class to handle different backup policies
1804 class BackupPolicy
1805 {
1806 public:
1807  enum Policy
1808  {
1809  Standard,
1810  TimeStamp
1811  };
1812  BackupPolicy()
1813  {
1814  policy = Standard;
1815  numberOfFiles = 1;
1816  useFCBakExtension = true;
1817  saveBackupDateFormat = "%Y%m%d-%H%M%S";
1818  }
1819  ~BackupPolicy() = default;
1820  void setPolicy(Policy p)
1821  {
1822  policy = p;
1823  }
1824  void setNumberOfFiles(int count)
1825  {
1826  numberOfFiles = count;
1827  }
1828  void useBackupExtension(bool on)
1829  {
1830  useFCBakExtension = on;
1831  }
1832  void setDateFormat(const std::string& fmt)
1833  {
1834  saveBackupDateFormat = fmt;
1835  }
1836  void apply(const std::string& sourcename, const std::string& targetname)
1837  {
1838  switch (policy) {
1839  case Standard:
1840  applyStandard(sourcename, targetname);
1841  break;
1842  case TimeStamp:
1843  applyTimeStamp(sourcename, targetname);
1844  break;
1845  }
1846  }
1847 
1848 private:
1849  void applyStandard(const std::string& sourcename, const std::string& targetname)
1850  {
1851  // if saving the project data succeeded rename to the actual file name
1852  Base::FileInfo fi(targetname);
1853  if (fi.exists()) {
1854  if (numberOfFiles > 0) {
1855  int nSuff = 0;
1856  std::string fn = fi.fileName();
1857  Base::FileInfo di(fi.dirPath());
1858  std::vector<Base::FileInfo> backup;
1859  std::vector<Base::FileInfo> files = di.getDirectoryContent();
1860  for (const Base::FileInfo& it : files) {
1861  std::string file = it.fileName();
1862  if (file.substr(0, fn.length()) == fn) {
1863  // starts with the same file name
1864  std::string suf(file.substr(fn.length()));
1865  if (!suf.empty()) {
1866  std::string::size_type nPos = suf.find_first_not_of("0123456789");
1867  if (nPos == std::string::npos) {
1868  // store all backup files
1869  backup.push_back(it);
1870  nSuff = std::max<int>(nSuff, std::atol(suf.c_str()));
1871  }
1872  }
1873  }
1874  }
1875 
1876  if (!backup.empty() && (int)backup.size() >= numberOfFiles) {
1877  // delete the oldest backup file we found
1878  Base::FileInfo del = backup.front();
1879  for (const Base::FileInfo& it : backup) {
1880  if (it.lastModified() < del.lastModified()) {
1881  del = it;
1882  }
1883  }
1884 
1885  del.deleteFile();
1886  fn = del.filePath();
1887  }
1888  else {
1889  // create a new backup file
1890  std::stringstream str;
1891  str << fi.filePath() << (nSuff + 1);
1892  fn = str.str();
1893  }
1894 
1895  if (!fi.renameFile(fn.c_str())) {
1896  Base::Console().Warning("Cannot rename project file to backup file\n");
1897  }
1898  }
1899  else {
1900  fi.deleteFile();
1901  }
1902  }
1903 
1904  Base::FileInfo tmp(sourcename);
1905  if (!tmp.renameFile(targetname.c_str())) {
1906  throw Base::FileException("Cannot rename tmp save file to project file",
1907  Base::FileInfo(targetname));
1908  }
1909  }
1910  void applyTimeStamp(const std::string& sourcename, const std::string& targetname)
1911  {
1912  Base::FileInfo fi(targetname);
1913 
1914  std::string fn = sourcename;
1915  std::string ext = fi.extension();
1916  std::string bn; // full path with no extension but with "."
1917  std::string pbn; // base name of the project + "."
1918  if (!ext.empty()) {
1919  bn = fi.filePath().substr(0, fi.filePath().length() - ext.length());
1920  pbn = fi.fileName().substr(0, fi.fileName().length() - ext.length());
1921  }
1922  else {
1923  bn = fi.filePath() + ".";
1924  pbn = fi.fileName() + ".";
1925  }
1926 
1927  bool backupManagementError = false; // Note error and report at the end
1928  if (fi.exists()) {
1929  if (numberOfFiles > 0) {
1930  // replace . by - in format to avoid . between base name and extension
1931  boost::replace_all(saveBackupDateFormat, ".", "-");
1932  {
1933  // Remove all extra backups
1934  std::string fn = fi.fileName();
1935  Base::FileInfo di(fi.dirPath());
1936  std::vector<Base::FileInfo> backup;
1937  std::vector<Base::FileInfo> files = di.getDirectoryContent();
1938  for (const Base::FileInfo& it : files) {
1939  if (it.isFile()) {
1940  std::string file = it.fileName();
1941  std::string fext = it.extension();
1942  std::string fextUp = fext;
1943  std::transform(fextUp.begin(),
1944  fextUp.end(),
1945  fextUp.begin(),
1946  (int (*)(int))toupper);
1947  // re-enforcing identification of the backup file
1948 
1949 
1950  // old case : the name starts with the full name of the project and
1951  // follows with numbers
1952  if ((startsWith(file, fn) && (file.length() > fn.length())
1953  && checkDigits(file.substr(fn.length())))
1954  ||
1955  // .FCBak case : The bame starts with the base name of the project +
1956  // "."
1957  // + complement with no "." + ".FCBak"
1958  ((fextUp == "FCBAK") && startsWith(file, pbn)
1959  && (checkValidComplement(file, pbn, fext)))) {
1960  backup.push_back(it);
1961  }
1962  }
1963  }
1964 
1965  if (!backup.empty() && (int)backup.size() >= numberOfFiles) {
1966  std::sort(backup.begin(), backup.end(), fileComparisonByDate);
1967  // delete the oldest backup file we found
1968  // Base::FileInfo del = backup.front();
1969  int nb = 0;
1970  for (Base::FileInfo& it : backup) {
1971  nb++;
1972  if (nb >= numberOfFiles) {
1973  try {
1974  if (!it.deleteFile()) {
1975  backupManagementError = true;
1976  Base::Console().Warning("Cannot remove backup file : %s\n",
1977  it.fileName().c_str());
1978  }
1979  }
1980  catch (...) {
1981  backupManagementError = true;
1982  Base::Console().Warning("Cannot remove backup file : %s\n",
1983  it.fileName().c_str());
1984  }
1985  }
1986  }
1987  }
1988  } // end remove backup
1989 
1990  // create a new backup file
1991  {
1992  int ext = 1;
1993  if (useFCBakExtension) {
1994  std::stringstream str;
1995  Base::TimeInfo ti = fi.lastModified();
1996  time_t s = ti.getTime_t();
1997  struct tm* timeinfo = localtime(&s);
1998  char buffer[100];
1999 
2000  strftime(buffer, sizeof(buffer), saveBackupDateFormat.c_str(), timeinfo);
2001  str << bn << buffer;
2002 
2003  fn = str.str();
2004  bool done = false;
2005 
2006  if ((fn.empty()) || (fn[fn.length() - 1] == ' ')
2007  || (fn[fn.length() - 1] == '-')) {
2008  if (fn[fn.length() - 1] == ' ') {
2009  fn = fn.substr(0, fn.length() - 1);
2010  }
2011  }
2012  else {
2013  if (!renameFileNoErase(fi, fn + ".FCBak")) {
2014  fn = fn + "-";
2015  }
2016  else {
2017  done = true;
2018  }
2019  }
2020 
2021  if (!done) {
2022  while (ext < numberOfFiles + 10) {
2023  if (renameFileNoErase(fi, fn + std::to_string(ext) + ".FCBak")) {
2024  break;
2025  }
2026  ext++;
2027  }
2028  }
2029  }
2030  else {
2031  // changed but simpler and solves also the delay sometimes introduced by
2032  // google drive
2033  while (ext < numberOfFiles + 10) {
2034  // linux just replace the file if exists, and then the existence is to
2035  // be tested before rename
2036  if (renameFileNoErase(fi, fi.filePath() + std::to_string(ext))) {
2037  break;
2038  }
2039  ext++;
2040  }
2041  }
2042 
2043  if (ext >= numberOfFiles + 10) {
2044  Base::Console().Error(
2045  "File not saved: Cannot rename project file to backup file\n");
2046  // throw Base::FileException("File not saved: Cannot rename project file to
2047  // backup file", fi);
2048  }
2049  }
2050  }
2051  else {
2052  try {
2053  fi.deleteFile();
2054  }
2055  catch (...) {
2056  Base::Console().Warning("Cannot remove backup file: %s\n",
2057  fi.fileName().c_str());
2058  backupManagementError = true;
2059  }
2060  }

2362 bool Document::afterRestore(const std::vector<DocumentObject*>& objArray, bool checkPartial)
2363 {
2364  checkPartial = checkPartial && testStatus(Document::PartialDoc);
2365  if (checkPartial && !d->touchedObjs.empty()) {
2366  return false;
2367  }
2368 
2369  // some link type property cannot restore link information until other
2370  // objects has been restored. For example, PropertyExpressionEngine and
2371  // PropertySheet with expression containing label reference. So we add the
2372  // Property::afterRestore() interface to let them sort it out. Note, this
2373  // API is not called in object dedpenency order, because the order
2374  // information is not ready yet.
2375  std::map<DocumentObject*, std::vector<App::Property*>> propMap;
2376  for (auto obj : objArray) {
2377  auto& props = propMap[obj];
2378  obj->getPropertyList(props);
2379  for (auto prop : props) {
2380  try {
2381  prop->afterRestore();
2382  }
2383  catch (const Base::Exception& e) {
2384  FC_ERR("Failed to restore " << obj->getFullName() << '.' << prop->getName() << ": "
2385  << e.what());
2386  }
2387  }
2388  }
2389 
2390  if (checkPartial && !d->touchedObjs.empty()) {
2391  // partial document touched, signal full reload
2392  return false;
2393  }
2394 
2395  std::set<DocumentObject*> objSet(objArray.begin(), objArray.end());
2396  auto objs = getDependencyList(objArray.empty() ? d->objectArray : objArray, DepSort);
2397  for (auto obj : objs) {
2398  if (objSet.find(obj) == objSet.end()) {
2399  continue;
2400  }
2401  try {
2402  for (auto prop : propMap[obj]) {
2403  prop->onContainerRestored();
2404  }
2405  bool touched = false;
2406  auto returnCode =
2407  obj->ExpressionEngine.execute(PropertyExpressionEngine::ExecuteOnRestore, &touched);
2408  if (returnCode != DocumentObject::StdReturn) {
2409  FC_ERR("Expression engine failed to restore " << obj->getFullName() << ": "
2410  << returnCode->Why);
2411  d->addRecomputeLog(returnCode);
2412  }
2413  obj->onDocumentRestored();
2414  if (touched) {
2415  d->touchedObjs.insert(obj);
2416  }
2417  }
2418  catch (const Base::Exception& e) {
2419  d->addRecomputeLog(e.what(), obj);
2420  FC_ERR("Failed to restore " << obj->getFullName() << ": " << e.what());
2421  }
2422  catch (std::exception& e) {
2423  d->addRecomputeLog(e.what(), obj);
2424  FC_ERR("Failed to restore " << obj->getFullName() << ": " << e.what());
2425  }
2426  catch (...) {
2427  d->addRecomputeLog("Unknown exception on restore", obj);
2428  FC_ERR("Failed to restore " << obj->getFullName() << ": " << "unknown exception");
2429  }
2430  if (obj->isValid()) {
2431  auto& props = propMap[obj];
2432  props.clear();
2433  // refresh properties in case the object changes its property list
2434  obj->getPropertyList(props);
2435  for (auto prop : props) {
2436  auto link = Base::freecad_dynamic_cast<PropertyLinkBase>(prop);
2437  int res;
2438  std::string errMsg;
2439  if (link && (res = link->checkRestore(&errMsg))) {
2440  d->touchedObjs.insert(obj);
2441  if (res == 1 || checkPartial) {
2442  FC_WARN(obj->getFullName() << '.' << prop->getName() << ": " << errMsg);
2443  setStatus(Document::LinkStampChanged, true);
2444  if (checkPartial) {
2445  return false;
2446  }
2447  }
2448  else {
2449  FC_ERR(obj->getFullName() << '.' << prop->getName() << ": " << errMsg);
2450  d->addRecomputeLog(errMsg, obj);
2451  setStatus(Document::PartialRestore, true);
2452  }
2453  }
2454  }
2455  }
2456 
2457  if (checkPartial && !d->touchedObjs.empty()) {
2458  // partial document touched, signal full reload
2459  return false;
2460  }
2461  else if (!d->touchedObjs.count(obj)) {
2462  obj->purgeTouched();
2463  }
2464 
2465  signalFinishRestoreObject(*obj);
2466  }
2467 
2468  d->touchedObjs.clear();
2469  return true;
2470 }

2558 void Document::getLinksTo(std::set<DocumentObject*>& links,
2559  const DocumentObject* obj,
2560  int options,
2561  int maxCount,
2562  const std::vector<DocumentObject*>& objs) const
2563 {
2564  std::map<const App::DocumentObject*, std::vector<App::DocumentObject*>> linkMap;
2565 
2566  for (auto o : !objs.empty() ? objs : d->objectArray) {
2567  if (o == obj) {
2568  continue;
2569  }
2570  auto linked = o;
2571  if (options & GetLinkArrayElement) {
2572  linked = o->getLinkedObject(false);
2573  }
2574  else {
2575  auto ext = o->getExtensionByType<LinkBaseExtension>(true);
2576  if (ext) {
2577  linked = ext->getTrueLinkedObject(false, nullptr, 0, true);
2578  }
2579  else {
2580  linked = o->getLinkedObject(false);
2581  }
2582  }
2583 
2584  if (linked && linked != o) {
2585  if (options & GetLinkRecursive) {
2586  linkMap[linked].push_back(o);
2587  }
2588  else if (linked == obj || !obj) {
2589  if ((options & GetLinkExternal) && linked->getDocument() == o->getDocument()) {
2590  continue;
2591  }
2592  else if (options & GetLinkedObject) {
2593  links.insert(linked);
2594  }
2595  else {
2596  links.insert(o);
2597  }
2598  if (maxCount && maxCount <= (int)links.size()) {
2599  return;
2600  }
2601  }
2602  }
2603  }
2604 
2605  if (!(options & GetLinkRecursive)) {
2606  return;
2607  }
2608 
2609  std::vector<const DocumentObject*> current(1, obj);
2610  for (int depth = 0; !current.empty(); ++depth) {
2611  if (!GetApplication().checkLinkDepth(depth, MessageOption::Error)) {
2612  break;
2613  }
2614  std::vector<const DocumentObject*> next;
2615  for (const App::DocumentObject* o : current) {
2616  auto iter = linkMap.find(o);
2617  if (iter == linkMap.end()) {
2618  continue;
2619  }
2620  for (App::DocumentObject* link : iter->second) {
2621  if (links.insert(link).second) {
2622  if (maxCount && maxCount <= (int)links.size()) {
2623  return;
2624  }
2625  next.push_back(link);
2626  }
2627  }
2628  }
2629  current = std::move(next);
2630  }
2631  return;
2632 }

2659 // This function unifies the old _rebuildDependencyList() and
2660 // getDependencyList(). The algorithm basically obtains the object dependency
2661 // by recrusivly visiting the OutList of each object in the given object array.
2662 // It makes sure to call getOutList() of each object once and only once, which
2663 // makes it much more efficient than calling getRecursiveOutList() on each
2664 // individual object.
2665 //
2666 // The problem with the original algorithm is that, it assumes the objects
2667 // inside any OutList are all within the given object array, so it does not
2668 // recursively call getOutList() on those dependent objects inside. This
2669 // assumption is broken by the introduction of PropertyXLink which can link to
2670 // external object.
2671 //
2672 static void _buildDependencyList(const std::vector<App::DocumentObject*>& objectArray,
2673  int options,
2674  std::vector<App::DocumentObject*>* depObjs,
2675  DependencyList* depList,
2676  std::map<DocumentObject*, Vertex>* objectMap,
2677  bool* touchCheck = nullptr)
2678 {
2679  std::map<DocumentObject*, std::vector<DocumentObject*>> outLists;
2680  std::deque<DocumentObject*> objs;
2681 
2682  if (objectMap) {
2683  objectMap->clear();
2684  }
2685  if (depList) {
2686  depList->clear();
2687  }
2688 
2689  int op = (options & Document::DepNoXLinked) ? DocumentObject::OutListNoXLinked : 0;
2690  for (auto obj : objectArray) {
2691  objs.push_back(obj);
2692  while (!objs.empty()) {
2693  auto obj = objs.front();
2694  objs.pop_front();
2695  if (!obj || !obj->isAttachedToDocument()) {
2696  continue;
2697  }
2698 
2699  auto it = outLists.find(obj);
2700  if (it != outLists.end()) {
2701  continue;
2702  }
2703 
2704  if (touchCheck) {
2705  if (obj->isTouched() || obj->mustExecute()) {
2706  // early termination on touch check
2707  *touchCheck = true;
2708  return;
2709  }
2710  }
2711  if (depObjs) {
2712  depObjs->push_back(obj);
2713  }
2714  if (objectMap && depList) {
2715  (*objectMap)[obj] = add_vertex(*depList);
2716  }
2717 
2718  auto& outList = outLists[obj];
2719  outList = obj->getOutList(op);
2720  objs.insert(objs.end(), outList.begin(), outList.end());
2721  }
2722  }
2723 
2724  if (objectMap && depList) {
2725  for (const auto& v : outLists) {
2726  for (auto obj : v.second) {
2727  if (obj && obj->isAttachedToDocument()) {
2728  add_edge((*objectMap)[v.first], (*objectMap)[obj], *depList);
2729  }
2730  }
2731  }
2732  }
2733 }

2735 std::vector<App::DocumentObject*>
2736 Document::getDependencyList(const std::vector<App::DocumentObject*>& objectArray, int options)
2737 {
2738  std::vector<App::DocumentObject*> ret;
2739  if (!(options & DepSort)) {
2740  _buildDependencyList(objectArray, options, &ret, nullptr, nullptr);
2741  return ret;
2742  }
2743 
2744  DependencyList depList;
2745  std::map<DocumentObject*, Vertex> objectMap;
2746  std::map<Vertex, DocumentObject*> vertexMap;
2747 
2748  _buildDependencyList(objectArray, options, nullptr, &depList, &objectMap);
2749 
2750  for (auto& v : objectMap) {
2751  vertexMap[v.second] = v.first;
2752  }
2753 
2754  std::list<Vertex> make_order;
2755  try {
2756  boost::topological_sort(depList, std::front_inserter(make_order));
2757  }

2761  // connected vertices as components, and therefore each component
2762  // forms a cycle.

2765  boost::strong_components(
2766  depList,
2767  boost::make_iterator_property_map(c.begin(),
2768  boost::get(boost::vertex_index, depList),
2769  c[0]));

2771  components[c[i]].push_back(i);

2774  FC_ERR("Dependency cycles: ");

2776  ss << std::endl;

2795  for (size_t i = 0; i < v.second.size(); ++i) {

2797  if (it == vertexMap.end()) {

2812  std::reverse(ret.begin(), ret.end());

2814  }
2815 
2816  for (std::list<Vertex>::reverse_iterator i = make_order.rbegin(); i != make_order.rend(); ++i) {
2817  ret.push_back(vertexMap[*i]);

2827 std::vector<App::Document*> Document::getDependentDocuments(std::vector<App::Document*> pending,
2828  bool sort)
2829 {
2830  DependencyList depList;
2831  std::map<Document*, Vertex> docMap;
2832  std::map<Vertex, Document*> vertexMap;
2833 
2834  std::vector<App::Document*> ret;
2835  if (pending.empty()) {
2836  return ret;
2837  }
2838 
2839  auto outLists = PropertyXLink::getDocumentOutList();
2840  std::set<App::Document*> docs;
2841  docs.insert(pending.begin(), pending.end());
2842  if (sort) {
2843  for (auto doc : pending) {
2844  docMap[doc] = add_vertex(depList);
2845  }
2846  }
2847  while (!pending.empty()) {
2848  auto doc = pending.back();
2849  pending.pop_back();
2850 
2851  auto it = outLists.find(doc);
2852  if (it == outLists.end()) {
2853  continue;
2854  }
2855 
2856  auto& vertex = docMap[doc];
2857  for (auto depDoc : it->second) {
2858  if (docs.insert(depDoc).second) {
2859  pending.push_back(depDoc);
2860  if (sort) {
2861  docMap[depDoc] = add_vertex(depList);
2862  }
2863  }
2864  add_edge(vertex, docMap[depDoc], depList);
2865  }
2866  }
2867 
2868  if (!sort) {
2869  ret.insert(ret.end(), docs.begin(), docs.end());
2870  return ret;
2871  }
2872 
2873  std::list<Vertex> make_order;
2874  try {
2875  boost::topological_sort(depList, std::front_inserter(make_order));
2876  }
2877  catch (const std::exception& e) {
2878  std::string msg("Document::getDependentDocuments: ");
2879  msg += e.what();
2880  throw Base::RuntimeError(msg);
2881  }
2882 
2883  for (auto& v : docMap) {
2884  vertexMap[v.second] = v.first;
2885  }
2886  for (auto rIt = make_order.rbegin(); rIt != make_order.rend(); ++rIt) {
2887  ret.push_back(vertexMap[*rIt]);
2888  }
2889  return ret;
2890 }

3392 {
3393  // topological sort algorithm described here:
3394  // https://de.wikipedia.org/wiki/Topologische_Sortierung#Algorithmus_f.C3.BCr_das_Topologische_Sortieren
3395  vector<App::DocumentObject*> ret;
3396  ret.reserve(objects.size());
3397  map<App::DocumentObject*, int> countMap;
3398 
3399  for (auto objectIt : objects) {
3400  // We now support externally linked objects
3401  // if(!obj->isAttachedToDocument() || obj->getDocument()!=this)
3402  if (!objectIt->isAttachedToDocument()) {
3403  continue;
3404  }
3405  // we need inlist with unique entries
3406  auto in = objectIt->getInList();
3407  std::sort(in.begin(), in.end());
3408  in.erase(std::unique(in.begin(), in.end()), in.end());

3410  countMap[objectIt] = in.size();

3412 
3413  auto rootObjeIt = find_if(countMap.begin(),
3414  countMap.end(),
3415  [](pair<App::DocumentObject*, int> count) -> bool {
3416  return count.second == 0;
3417  });
3418

3421  return ret;

3423 
3424  while (rootObjeIt != countMap.end()) {
3425  rootObjeIt->second = rootObjeIt->second - 1;
3426 
3427  // we need outlist with unique entries
3428  auto out = rootObjeIt->first->getOutList();
3429  std::sort(out.begin(), out.end());
3430  out.erase(std::unique(out.begin(), out.end()), out.end());
3431 
3432  for (auto outListIt : out) {
3433  auto outListMapIt = countMap.find(outListIt);
3434  if (outListMapIt != countMap.end()) {
3435  outListMapIt->second = outListMapIt->second - 1;
3436  }
3437  }
3438  ret.push_back(rootObjeIt->first);
3439 
3440  rootObjeIt = find_if(countMap.begin(),
3441  countMap.end(),
3442  [](pair<App::DocumentObject*, int> count) -> bool {
3443  return count.second == 0;
3444  });
3445  }
3446 
3447  return ret;
3448 }

3460 // call the recompute of the Feature and handle the exceptions and errors.
3461 int Document::_recomputeFeature(DocumentObject* Feat)
3462 {
3463  FC_LOG("Recomputing " << Feat->getFullName());
3464 
3465  DocumentObjectExecReturn* returnCode = nullptr;
3466  try {
3467  returnCode = Feat->ExpressionEngine.execute(PropertyExpressionEngine::ExecuteNonOutput);
3468  if (returnCode == DocumentObject::StdReturn) {
3469  returnCode = Feat->recompute();
3470  if (returnCode == DocumentObject::StdReturn) {
3471  returnCode =
3472  Feat->ExpressionEngine.execute(PropertyExpressionEngine::ExecuteOutput);
3473  }
3474  }
3475  }
3476  catch (Base::AbortException& e) {
3477  e.ReportException();
3478  FC_LOG("Failed to recompute " << Feat->getFullName() << ": " << e.what());
3479  d->addRecomputeLog("User abort", Feat);
3480  return -1;
3481  }
3482  catch (const Base::MemoryException& e) {
3483  FC_ERR("Memory exception in " << Feat->getFullName() << " thrown: " << e.what());
3484  d->addRecomputeLog("Out of memory exception", Feat);
3485  return 1;
3486  }
3487  catch (Base::Exception& e) {
3488  e.ReportException();
3489  FC_LOG("Failed to recompute " << Feat->getFullName() << ": " << e.what());
3490  d->addRecomputeLog(e.what(), Feat);
3491  return 1;
3492  }
3493  catch (std::exception& e) {
3494  FC_ERR("exception in " << Feat->getFullName() << " thrown: " << e.what());
3495  d->addRecomputeLog(e.what(), Feat);
3496  return 1;
3497  }
3498 #ifndef FC_DEBUG
3499  catch (...) {
3500  FC_ERR("Unknown exception in " << Feat->getFullName() << " thrown");
3501  d->addRecomputeLog("Unknown exception!", Feat);
3502  return 1;
3503  }
3504 #endif
3505 
3506  if (returnCode == DocumentObject::StdReturn) {
3507  Feat->resetError();
3508  }
3509  else {
3510  returnCode->Which = Feat;
3511  d->addRecomputeLog(returnCode);
3512  FC_LOG("Failed to recompute " << Feat->getFullName() << ": " << returnCode->Why);
3513  return 1;
3514  }
3515  return 0;
3516 }

3836 void Document::removeObject(const char* sName)
3837 {
3838  auto pos = d->objectMap.find(sName);
3839 
3840  // name not found?
3841  if (pos == d->objectMap.end()) {
3842  return;
3843  }
3844 
3845  if (pos->second->testStatus(ObjectStatus::PendingRecompute)) {
3846  // TODO: shall we allow removal if there is active undo transaction?
3847  FC_MSG("pending remove of " << sName << " after recomputing document " << getName());
3848  d->pendingRemove.emplace_back(pos->second);
3849  return;
3850  }
3851 
3852  TransactionLocker tlock;
3853 
3854  _checkTransaction(pos->second, nullptr, __LINE__);
3855 
3856  if (d->activeObject == pos->second) {
3857  d->activeObject = nullptr;
3858  }
3859 
3860  // Mark the object as about to be deleted
3861  pos->second->setStatus(ObjectStatus::Remove, true);
3862  if (!d->undoing && !d->rollback) {
3863  pos->second->unsetupObject();
3864  }
3865 
3866  signalDeletedObject(*(pos->second));
3867 
3868  // do no transactions if we do a rollback!
3869  if (!d->rollback && d->activeUndoTransaction) {
3870  // in this case transaction delete or save the object
3871  signalTransactionRemove(*pos->second, d->activeUndoTransaction);
3872  }
3873  else {
3874  // if not saved in undo -> delete object
3875  signalTransactionRemove(*pos->second, 0);
3876  }
3877 
3878 #ifdef USE_OLD_DAG
3879  if (!d->vertexMap.empty()) {
3880  // recompute of document is running
3881  for (std::map<Vertex, DocumentObject*>::iterator it = d->vertexMap.begin();
3882  it != d->vertexMap.end();
3883  ++it) {
3884  if (it->second == pos->second) {
3885  it->second = 0; // just nullify the pointer
3886  break;
3887  }
3888  }
3889  }
3890 #endif // USE_OLD_DAG
3891 
3892  // Before deleting we must nullify all dependent objects
3893  breakDependency(pos->second, true);
3894 
3895  // and remove the tip if needed
3896  if (Tip.getValue() && strcmp(Tip.getValue()->getNameInDocument(), sName) == 0) {
3897  Tip.setValue(nullptr);
3898  TipName.setValue("");
3899  }
3900 
3901  // remove the ID before possibly deleting the object
3902  d->objectIdMap.erase(pos->second->_Id);
3903  // Unset the bit to be on the safe side
3904  pos->second->setStatus(ObjectStatus::Remove, false);
3905 
3906  // do no transactions if we do a rollback!
3907  std::unique_ptr<DocumentObject> tobedestroyed;
3908  if (!d->rollback) {
3909  // Undo stuff
3910  if (d->activeUndoTransaction) {
3911  // in this case transaction delete or save the object
3912  d->activeUndoTransaction->addObjectNew(pos->second);
3913  }
3914  else {
3915  // if not saved in undo -> delete object later
3916  std::unique_ptr<DocumentObject> delobj(pos->second);
3917  tobedestroyed.swap(delobj);
3918  tobedestroyed->setStatus(ObjectStatus::Destroy, true);
3919  }
3920  }
3921 
3922  for (std::vector<DocumentObject*>::iterator obj = d->objectArray.begin();
3923  obj != d->objectArray.end();
3924  ++obj) {
3925  if (*obj == pos->second) {
3926  d->objectArray.erase(obj);
3927  break;
3928  }
3929  }
3930 
3931  // In case the object gets deleted the pointer must be nullified
3932  if (tobedestroyed) {
3933  tobedestroyed->pcNameInDocument = nullptr;
3934  }
3935  d->objectMap.erase(pos);
3936 }

4029 Document::copyObject(const std::vector<DocumentObject*>& objs, bool recursive, bool returnAll)

4050  memsize += it->getMemSize();

4053  // if less than ~10 MB
4054  bool use_buffer = (memsize < 0xA00000);

4070  std::istream istr(nullptr);

4076  Base::ofstream ostr(fi, std::ios::out | std::ios::binary);
4077  exportObjects(deps, ostr);

4079 
4080  Base::ifstream istr(fi, std::ios::in | std::ios::binary);
4081  imported = md.importObjects(istr);

4085  return imported;
4086  }
4087 
4088  std::unordered_map<App::DocumentObject*, size_t> indices;

4101 std::vector<App::DocumentObject*>
4102 Document::importLinks(const std::vector<App::DocumentObject*>& objArray)
4103 {
4104  std::set<App::DocumentObject*> links;
4105  getLinksTo(links, nullptr, GetLinkExternal, 0, objArray);
4106 
4107  std::vector<App::DocumentObject*> objs;
4108  objs.insert(objs.end(), links.begin(), links.end());
4109  objs = App::Document::getDependencyList(objs);
4110  if (objs.empty()) {
4111  FC_ERR("nothing to import");
4112  return objs;
4113  }
4114 
4115  for (auto it = objs.begin(); it != objs.end();) {
4116  auto obj = *it;
4117  if (obj->getDocument() == this) {
4118  it = objs.erase(it);
4119  continue;
4120  }
4121  ++it;
4122  if (obj->testStatus(App::PartialObject)) {
4123  throw Base::RuntimeError(
4124  "Cannot import partial loaded object. Please reload the current document");
4125  }
4126  }
4127 
4128  Base::FileInfo fi(App::Application::getTempFileName());
4129  {
4130  // save stuff to temp file
4131  Base::ofstream str(fi, std::ios::out | std::ios::binary);
4132  MergeDocuments mimeView(this);
4133  exportObjects(objs, str);
4134  str.close();
4135  }
4136  Base::ifstream str(fi, std::ios::in | std::ios::binary);
4137  MergeDocuments mimeView(this);
4138  objs = mimeView.importObjects(str);
4139  str.close();
4140  fi.deleteFile();
4141 
4142  const auto& nameMap = mimeView.getNameMap();
4143 
4144  // First, find all link type properties that needs to be changed
4145  std::map<App::Property*, std::unique_ptr<App::Property>> propMap;
4146  std::vector<App::Property*> propList;
4147  for (auto obj : links) {
4148  propList.clear();
4149  obj->getPropertyList(propList);
4150  for (auto prop : propList) {
4151  auto linkProp = Base::freecad_dynamic_cast<PropertyLinkBase>(prop);
4152  if (linkProp && !prop->testStatus(Property::Immutable) && !obj->isReadOnly(prop)) {
4153  auto copy = linkProp->CopyOnImportExternal(nameMap);
4154  if (copy) {
4155  propMap[linkProp].reset(copy);
4156  }
4157  }
4158  }
4159  }
4160 
4161  // Then change them in one go. Note that we don't make change in previous
4162  // loop, because a changed link property may break other depending link
4163  // properties, e.g. a link sub referring to some sub object of an xlink, If
4164  // that sub object is imported with a different name, and xlink is changed
4165  // before this link sub, it will break.
4166  for (auto& v : propMap) {
4167  v.first->Paste(*v.second);
4168  }
4169 
4170  return objs;
4171 }

4173 DocumentObject* Document::moveObject(DocumentObject* obj, bool recursive)
4174 {
4175  if (!obj) {
4176  return nullptr;
4177  }
4178  Document* that = obj->getDocument();
4179  if (that == this) {
4180  return nullptr; // nothing todo
4181  }
4182 
4183  // True object move without copy is only safe when undo is off on both
4184  // documents.
4185  if (!recursive && !d->iUndoMode && !that->d->iUndoMode && !that->d->rollback) {
4186  // all object of the other document that refer to this object must be nullified
4187  that->breakDependency(obj, false);
4188  std::string objname = getUniqueObjectName(obj->getNameInDocument());
4189  that->_removeObject(obj);
4190  this->_addObject(obj, objname.c_str());
4191  obj->setDocument(this);
4192  return obj;
4193  }
4194 
4195  std::vector<App::DocumentObject*> deps;
4196  if (recursive) {
4197  deps = getDependencyList({obj}, DepNoXLinked | DepSort);
4198  }
4199  else {
4200  deps.push_back(obj);
4201  }
4202 
4203  auto objs = copyObject(deps, false);
4204  if (objs.empty()) {
4205  return nullptr;
4206  }
4207  // Some object may delete its children if deleted, so we collect the IDs
4208  // or all depending objects for safety reason.
4209  std::vector<int> ids;
4210  ids.reserve(deps.size());
4211  for (auto o : deps) {
4212  ids.push_back(o->getID());
4213  }
4214 
4215  // We only remove object if it is the moving object or it has no
4216  // depending objects, i.e. an empty inList, which is why we need to
4217  // iterate the depending list backwards.
4218  for (auto iter = ids.rbegin(); iter != ids.rend(); ++iter) {
4219  auto o = that->getObjectByID(*iter);
4220  if (!o) {
4221  continue;
4222  }
4223  if (iter == ids.rbegin() || o->getInList().empty()) {
4224  that->removeObject(o->getNameInDocument());
4225  }
4226  }
4227  return objs.back();
4228 }

4479 std::vector<std::list<App::DocumentObject*>>
4480 Document::getPathsByOutList(const App::DocumentObject* from, const App::DocumentObject* to) const
4481 {
4482  std::map<const DocumentObject*, size_t> indexMap;
4483  for (size_t i = 0; i < d->objectArray.size(); ++i) {
4484  indexMap[d->objectArray[i]] = i;
4485  }
4486 
4487  std::vector<Node> all_nodes(d->objectArray.size());
4488  for (size_t i = 0; i < d->objectArray.size(); ++i) {
4489  DocumentObject* obj = d->objectArray[i];
4490  std::vector<DocumentObject*> outList = obj->getOutList();
4491  for (auto it : outList) {
4492  all_nodes[i].push_back(indexMap[it]);
4493  }
4494  }
4495 
4496  std::vector<std::list<App::DocumentObject*>> array;
4497  if (from == to) {
4498  return array;
4499  }
4500 
4501  size_t index_from = indexMap[from];
4502  size_t index_to = indexMap[to];
4503  Path tmp;
4504  std::vector<Path> all_paths;
4505  DocumentP::findAllPathsAt(all_nodes, index_from, all_paths, tmp);
4506 
4507  for (const Path& it : all_paths) {
4508  Path::const_iterator jt = std::find(it.begin(), it.end(), index_to);
4509  if (jt != it.end()) {
4510  std::list<App::DocumentObject*> path;
4511  for (Path::const_iterator kt = it.begin(); kt != jt; ++kt) {
4512  path.push_back(d->objectArray[*kt]);
4513  }
4514 
4515  path.push_back(d->objectArray[*jt]);
4516  array.push_back(path);
4517  }
4518  }
4519 
4520  // remove duplicates
4521  std::sort(array.begin(), array.end());
4522  array.erase(std::unique(array.begin(), array.end()), array.end());
4523 
4524  return array;
4525 }
